{"tid":1040183,"cid":22,"subCid":0,"title":"USB 3.2 D名仲衰過 USB 3.1 GEN1 GEN2","createTime":"2019-02-28T02:01:07.000Z","updateTime":"2019-12-12T14:59:28.000Z","uid":37232,"like":9,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"9a81bba06084baba4ec70fa5179fbc65dd745c67","tid":1040183,"uid":37232,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-28T02:01:07.000Z","msg":"The USB 3.2 specification absorbed all prior 3.x specifications. USB 3.2 identifies three<br />\ntransfer rates, <span style=\"color: red;\">USB 3.2 Gen 1 at 5Gbps, USB 3.2 Gen 2 at 10Gbps and USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 at<br />\n20Gbps.</span> It is important that vendors clearly communicate the performance signaling that a<br />\nproduct delivers in the product&rsquo;s packaging, advertising content, and any other marketing<br />\nmaterials.<br />\n<br />\n&bull; USB 3.2 Gen 1<br />\no Product capability: product signals at 5Gbps<br />\no Marketing name: SuperSpeed USB<br />\n&bull; USB 3.2 Gen 2<br />\no Product capability: product signals at 10Gbps<br />\no Marketing name: SuperSpeed USB 10Gbps<br />\n&bull; USB 3.2 Gen 2x2<br />\no Product capability: product signals at 20Gbps<br />\no Marketing name: SuperSpeed USB 20Gbps<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.usb.org/sites/default/files/usb_3_2_language_product_and_packaging_guidelines_final.pdf\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usb.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fusb_3_2_language_product_and_packaging_guidelines_final.pdf&d=HVFDXqn9keSrFxh6Mt7Td8%2BxtiM4uRDursPVmWLIdz4%3D&h=7f5a6c75\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.usb.org/sites/default/files/usb_3_2_language_product_and_packaging_guidelines_final.pdf</a><br />\n<br />\nON9無上限<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e39f60d2b59feb2dde1526b5b0af60dba9733ec7","tid":1040183,"uid":37232,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-28T05:46:40.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"p